name: Fortune Cookie
directions: In the back down the hall by the kitchen.
comment:
Don't have to be a paying customer. Staff is cool about whichever one yo
u want to go in. Girls is cleaner though.

name: Ozark Mountain Bagel Co.
directions: in the back, to the right of the register
comment: they’re nice people and a local business, probably don’t care if you just need to go. 2 separate gender-neutral bathrooms

name: Target
directions: In the back near the personal care and pharmacy area.  Large signs are changing from the ceiling to point you towards them.

name: Main Street Creamery
comment: Paying customers only

name: Seize the Clay
directions: Go all the way back and go in the door, then turn left.
comment: It's a pottery/painting place, but if you are going there they have one gender neutral bathroom because the women's is closed. You could trying a soda from the vending machine or asking questions, though. Best of luck!

name: Campbell City Hall
directions: Upper floor of City Hall, in the atrium.
comment: Open during normal 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM business hours.

name: Hammarskjold high school
directions: To the left of the library

name: Doling Senior Center
directions: Walk in and to the left down the hall, between the arts and crafts room and the pool room

name: Westside 66
directions: As you walk in the door there's a small hallway with a bench and a single stall restroom.

name: Crumpers
directions: It’s in a smaller building  next to the restaurant.

name: Library bathroom
directions: It's in the basement of the library in front of the elevators. Stair directions: Take a left after exiting the stairs, and then immediately take another left and it's the first door.
comment: The door to the stairs is wooden, and it's in the area directly to the left of the main entrance when walking in. The door is not labeled, but it has a small square window near the top of it.

name: Starbucks
comment: Code posted on the door

name: Peck Farm Park, 4038 Kaneville Rd, Geneva, IL 60134, USA
directions: East of the parking lot near the orientation center

name: Taylor Education Building, Lexington, KY 40508, USA
directions: To the left of the auditorium. Has a sign you can flip to say occupied/vacant.

name: Batch Bakehouse
directions: Directly beyond the front door.

name: National Museum of Natural History
directions: This is a “companion care” restroom located off the Sant Ocean Hall on the museum’s first floor. The door is located just to the right of the women’s room entrance.
comment: Museum admission is free, but you will have to go through security to enter.

name: Scoff Troff Cafe
directions: In the back, to the left.
comment: Paying customers only. Two unisex stalls (no single-sex ones), shared bathroom.

name: Katana
directions: Hallway in very back
comment: Not actually single stall, but the entire bathroom is lockable (at least the men's room is)

name: Maxine’s
directions: At the end of the bar under the balcony

name: 904 Lexington Ave, New York, NY 10065, USA
directions: Thomas hunter 6th floor and 3rd floor

name: Starbucks Strawberry Village
comment: very nice - very open, wide welcoming space.

name: Chichester Train Station
directions: platform 1 (ticket office side) ladies right at the end of the platform nearest the crossing mens i believe is in the waiting room towards the other end of the platform
comment: may need to buy a ticket unless the barriers are open.

name: Crown Shopping Centre, Tescos Extra/Cafe
directions: walk into the centre turn right near the cafe the toilets are to the right.
comment: this is not in tescos so no need to buy anything. Just be prepared for a queue to the ladies

name: Red House Boutique
directions: Disabled Toilet to the right of the pub. Ladies and Mens through the door to the left behind the bar walk up the stairs.
comment: seems to be a safe place for LGBTQIA+ if unsure use the disabled toilet but nicer ones are upstairs.

name: Restaurant Depot
directions: Right next to the gendered restrooms
comment: You need to have a buyer card to shop here, but no one checks on the way in.

name: The Old Bank
directions: straight past the bar down stairs. Ladies in front of you. Mens to the right.
comment: no signs saying you need to be a customer but just wait for the bar to be a bit busy it makes it a lot easier if your not a customer.

name: McDonalds
directions: Towards the tills to the right hand side.
comment: seems like it doesn't matter if your a customer just walk in and slip by.

name: Leon
directions: Right next to the till on the left. often busy enough that they won't notice if you aren't a customer.

name: Johnson County Public Library
directions: Upstairs (2nd floor) and behind you as you come up the last stair

name: Mimimi
directions: through doors to left just as you walk in
comment: only open sometimes.

name: El Ojú
directions: turn right after the bar/till. two cubicle spaces through the doors.
comment: vegan tapas!

name: Brighthelm Church and Community Centre
directions: Located near cafe area behind a section wall, just before the stair doors.

name: CC:/ Side Quest
directions: Through door and left around room. Several cubicles and one accessible.
comment: LGBT+ board game venue

name: The Marlborough
directions: Through front doors, take a left and go to the end of the room. bathroom converted to neutral.
comment: It's an LGBT+ venue and they're very friendly.

name: Small Batch Coffee Co
directions: Through front doors, bathroom door is left of the till. bathroom itself is communal sink and multiple cubicles that have male and female symbols half an half, but a shared space so nobody pays attention. also has accessible to the side.
comment: bathroom can be accessed if you're in the MyHotel venue next door also.

name: The Bee's Mouth
directions: The venue goes downward so the first floor is the top. follow the stairs at the back down and round. single cubicle is neutral on your right side. covered floor to ceiling in pictures of steve buscemi.
comment: since it's a bar, nobody notices or cares if you're a customer if it's fairly busy.

name: Brighton Dome
directions: Second floor, i think right wing. converted multi-cubicle into gender neutral. sign outside explains and says anybody with problems can use any other bathroom on the premises.

name: Presuming Ed's Coffee House
directions: through front door, the left set of doors ahead of you. end of corridor is two cubicle neutral room with neutral disabled before it.
comment: haven't ever noticed them care if i pay but i'm there a lot because i live down the road

name: Paradise Pantry
directions: One side is a restaurant, one side is a wine & cheese shop. In the back of the restaurant side is a single occupancy gender neutral restroom.
comment: If you entered through shop side, you could probably cut through to the restroom pretty easily without having to buy anything. Plus, cheese samples!

name: Jimmy’s Slice
directions: All the way to the back
comment: Casual pizza joint with single gender neutral restroom

name: San Buenaventura State Beach - public restrooms
directions: There is a fee to enter the parking lot, but there’s also neighborhood free parking next to the camp/day use area. After the kiosk, follow the main road til coming to a large parking area. The restrooms are odd upright tubular shaped buildings.
comment: Each “tube” is a single occupancy, gender neutral basic beach toilet. There’s also an open air shower with hot water. Could be a good stop if riding along the bike path that also runs along the beach/coast.

name: Surfer’s Knoll Beach - public restrooms
directions: Just next to the small beach parking lot.
comment: There are 4 single occupancy gender neutral restrooms. Usually no soap, and just air dry hands.

name: 545 N Citrus Ave, Crystal River, FL 34428, USA
TK Maxx
directions: Top floor to the left of the escalators

name: Physics Building
directions: Enter the main doors and turn left. The door is on your left as you reach the cafe seating area.
comment: Only available when university is open.

name: Stepwork
directions: The bathrooms are in a corridor that's on your left when you walk inside.
comment: Stepwork is a clinic for trans people. You can use the bathroom that you want to use, even though they are gendered.

name: Student Union
directions: Most floors have at least one neutral bathroom. Ground floor bathrooms can be found a) directly inside the side door, and b) beside the gendered bathrooms used for Club 601.

name: 't Frietmanneke
directions: On the left side of the counter is a little corridor. The bathrooms are on the left hand side in this corridor.
comment: You have to be a paying customer.

name: Jack Cole Building
directions: On the right, just past the gendered bathrooms and staircase.
comment: Need a keycard to enter the building, but Monday-Friday 9am-5pm it should be busy enough to get in as someone else is entering/leaving.

name: Library Harderwijk
directions: On the first floor of the library part of the city hall. Just opposite of the stairs.
comment: Only available at library opening hours, these are different to the opening hours of the city hall.

name: O'Tacos
directions: On the right in the back

name: Subway
directions: On the first floor next to the stairs

name: TK Maxx
directions: Top floor

name: Greyhound Bus Station
directions: Just past vending machines on the right.
comment: Gender neutral bathroom is always locked. Not sure if you have to ask for keys or something. Been harassed in the men’s restroom.

name: County clothing
directions: Down the ramp first door on right
comment: Come get some free clothes and home goods while there

name: Paddy’s Cocktail Bar
directions: Enter through the back parking lot, through the patio, and the restroom is directly inside
comment: Local gay bar. One single occupancy gender neutral restroom, and a men’s room with a stall with no door.

name: La Frutileta Michoacana
comment: The best paletas (Mexican popsicles) in town! And a single occupancy gender neutral restroom to boot!

name: Topa Topa Brewing Co
directions: Just inside, on the left
comment: Single occupancy gender neutral restroom. Great brewery!

name: MadeWest Brewing Co
comment: 3 single occupancy restrooms. 2 are gendered, one is gender neutral

name: Full Tilt Ice Cream
directions: In the back, past all the pinball games

name: The Monkey Bridge
directions: Towards the back, past all the tables, on the left

name: Reubens Brews
comment: Can’t remember if they’re gender neutral or not, but there are 2 single occupancy restrooms.

name: Rainbow Bridge Grocery
comment: Get key from cashier

name: La Fondita
comment: Paying customers only, get a token from the server/cashier

name: 9 Village Loop Drive, Grand Canyon Village, AZ 86023, USA
directions: Walk into the bright angle lodge and turn left, towards the history room.

name: Yahara House
comment: Need to take a tour of the Clubhouse before using the restroom; is a community mental health program for adults with mental health concerns.

name: Dublin Methodist Hospital
directions: Main Level - two gender neutral restrooms between help/welcome desk and emergency room

name: Wander North Georgia
directions: In the back of the store on the left hand side, through the doorway.
comment: You don’t have to be a customer. The staff is so friendly. If you need a safe space let them know.

name: Sport clips
directions: Past the chairs to the left
comment: Just say you’re already on the wait list

name: US-160 &, US-163, Kayenta, AZ 86033, United States
directions: Go into the convenience store. It’s at the back.
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Bookman’s
directions: In the back of the store, two single stall gender neutral facilities.

name: The Chateau
comment: Queer bar/club, 18+ open only weekends, not accessible (basement)

name: Beta boulders
comment: For beta boulder customers

name: Olivaceous i Kronen
comment: Only for customers
